<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-10-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-10-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="1163" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1163">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/6801d.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Consul <persName type="to">Letcher</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-10-09">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 9, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Advise confidentially all Americans in your district to leave Chihuahua
                            for border. You are instructed arrange for closing Parral agency, and
                            advise agent and Americans in his district to withdraw therefrom. You
                            are further instructed to close consulate and leave for border.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>